The color (L*, a*, b*, and ΔE*) of the edible films was measured by a chromameter (CR-400, Konica Minolta, Tokyo, Japan) and calibrated with a white standard plate (L* = 93.25, a* = −5.21, b* = 7.68). Five positions were chosen randomly on each sample’s surface and averaged. The total color difference (ΔE*) was calculated by the following equation45:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
